I can hear you, but I won’t. Some look for trouble...while others don’t. There’s a thousand reasons I should go about my day.....and ignore you’re whispers which I wish would go go away. You’re not a voice, your just a ringing in my ear, and if I heard you. Which I don’t. I’m spoken for I fear, everyone I’ve ever loved is here within’ these walls, I’m sorry secret siren but I’m blocking out you calls, I’ve had my adventure I don’t need something new, I’m afraid of what I’m risking if I follow you. Into the unkno-o-own into the unkno-o-own into the unkno-o-o-o-o-own. What do you want? Because you’ve been keeping me awake...are you here to distract me, so I make a big mistake. Or are you someone out there, who’s a little bit like me. Who knows I’m not where I’m supposed to be...every day’s a little harder. As I feel my power grow, don’t you know there’s part of me that longs to go, into the unknown! Into the unknown! Into the unknown! Are you out there?Do you know me? Can you feel me? Can you show me? Where are you going? Dom’t leave me alone! How do I follow you? Into the unknown!






(Also, did you know I was born BEFORE the Frozen movies? I’m older than them...
